title: Check security staff have a licence to work

heading_context: Check security staff have a licence to work
chunks.html_content:
You must check if someone has the correct security licence before hiring them for private security work. If they don’t, you must make sure they get training and a licence.

Search the register of Security Industry Authority (SIA) licence holders, to check whether someone has a licence to be a:

  • security guard
  • door supervisor
  • close protection operative (sometimes known as a ‘bodyguard’)
  • CCTV operator or to work in public space surveillance
  • key holder
  • guard who transports cash and valuables
  • in Northern Ireland, a worker who clamps wheels, moves vehicles and charges for their release

heading_context: Check security staff have a licence to work
chunks.html_content: You could be fined or sent to prison if you pay someone to work in security without the right SIA licence.
chunks.plain_content:
Check security staff have a licence to work
You could be fined or sent to prison if you pay someone to work in security without the right SIA licence.

heading_context: Check security staff have a licence to work
chunks.html_content:
To find someone on the register you need either:

  • their 16-digit SIA licence number
  • their surname and other personal details, such as their date of birth and security role

Start now on the SIA form

To find a security company approved by the SIA, use their register of security contractors.
